Category: RGNT
Title: DNA Shredding Buffer for Gene Shuffling
Description: A simple dilution of DNAseI in glycerin for partial DNA digestion used in Gene Shuffling techniques.
1. To a sterile 1.5mL microcentrifuge tube, add 1000uL of sterile 50% glycerin solution.
2. Remove 1uL of glycerin from the tube.
3. Add 1uL of DNAseI (New England Biolabs Cat# M0303S) to the glycerin solution.
4. Vortex vigorously to mix the enzyme in the viscous glycerin solution.
5. Store at -20C indefinitely.
END
